### Patient Authentication API Tests

### 1. Register a new patient
POST {{host}}/api/patient-auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "middleName": "Michael",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "userName": "johndoe123",
  "password": "SecurePassword123",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "gender": 1,
  "dateOfBirth": "1990-05-15T00:00:00Z"
}

### 2. Verify OTP (use the OTP returned from registration)
POST {{host}}/api/patient-auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "otp": "123456"
}

### 3. Login with phone number and password
POST {{host}}/api/patient-auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "password": "SecurePassword123"
}

### 4. Check if phone number exists
GET {{host}}/api/patient-auth/phone-exists?phoneNumber=+1234567890

### 5. Check if username exists
GET {{host}}/api/patient-auth/username-exists?userName=johndoe123

